Will there be a year-end rally on the stock exchange? Experts divided by the sub-prime crisis.
Less than five weeks from the end of the fiscal year, investors are already rubbing their hands hoping for the arrival of the traditional year-end rally.
However, this year the experts are not as sure as this will happen.
Banif believes that "from a statistical point of view, December on the stock market generally has a positive behaviour.
However, forecasts should not be made solely on the basis of statistics, since, given the current context, uncertainties are on the markets, at least in the short term."
