"It's not the best thing," says the expert.
Ibex, the Spanish stock market index, has lost almost 4% since 8 November when the index closed at 15,945.7 points.
However, not all experts have such a negative view.
Intermoney analyst Juan Solana believes that Ibex 35 could close the year at 16,000 points due to the reorganization of portfolios and the traditional contributions to pension plans that occur every year during these dates.
