What assurance does it suit me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, involves a significant expenditure which will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, seniority of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Here, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es included más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise materializes in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the insurance price, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, seniority of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower rate of claims due to their prudence.
Similarly, by using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
Here we will describe the most significant variables when choosing one or other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when entering into a contract with insurance at an affordable price, as may be the low level of experience in driving and the seniority of the driver's licence.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is to provide insurance at any risk, other, more cost-effective options exist.
The most anticipated drivers can opt for any risk insurance with deductible, so that they get insurance coverage at any risk but at a more accessible price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim paid by the customer will be determined according to the value of the premium, which will be higher and the amount will be lower," says Luis Noguera, the Spanish manager of First Europa, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be careful and avoid claims as far as possible, since this will affect the premium, which can reduce the insurance price in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses ", clarified Noguera.
After 25 years, it becomes easier for drivers to make a contract with insurance, since the loss rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose any risk insurance with deductible.
"Normally young people cannot take advantage of the experience acquired in advance after an accident", says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable for the client to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his or her economic situation permits.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be those with the lowest loss rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be any risk insurance with deductible (which could be 300 euros), or third-party insurance extended from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more relaxed conduct and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury to assume a larger amount of franchises," Justice Luis Noguera.
For retirees, any risk insurance with deductible is preferable (by being 150 euros), or extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible losses, but also because it represents a great expense, which is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
